  },
  {
    title: 'Wild Turkey',
    description: 'Spring gobbler season brings birds working the ridges at dawn. The mature hardwoods make turkey hunting particularly good here. Fall turkey season is also available.',
    notes: 'Ridge tops in mature timber for roosting birds. Listen for gobbles at dawn and set up between the roost and where they want to go. Don\'t overcall — let them come to you.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Black Bear',
    description: 'Nicholas County is in West Virginia\'s bear zone. Multiple seasons run mid-September through December. Bear Damage Stamp required in addition to hunting license.',
